@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>CrowdQR is an open-source project committed to transparency and user privacy. This privacy policy explains how we handle any information that might be collected through our application.</p>

            <h2>Data Collection</h2>
            <p>CrowdQR is designed with privacy in mind:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>We do not collect personal information</li>
                <li>We do not track user behavior</li>
                <li>We do not sell or share any data with third parties</li>
                <li>We do not use cookies for tracking purposes</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Technical Data</h2>
            <p>The application may automatically collect some technical information necessary for its operation:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Basic usage data required for the application to function</li>
                <li>Temporary session data that is cleared when you close the application</li>
                <li>Error logs that help us improve the application's stability</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Open Source Commitment</h2>
            <p>As an open-source project:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Our entire codebase is publicly available for review</li>
                <li>We welcome community contributions and scrutiny of our privacy practices</li>
                <li>Any future changes to our privacy policy will be transparent and documented</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Contact</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about our privacy practices, you can:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Open an issue on our GitHub repository</li>
                <li>Review our source code</li>
                <li>Contribute to improving our privacy measures</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>This privacy policy may be updated occasionally to reflect changes in our practices or improvements in our privacy measures. All changes will be documented in our project's version control system.</p>

            <p class="mt-4"><small>Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</small></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
